00:18:46,310 --> 00:18:50,041
You talked this over
with Crawford. Right?

285
00:18:50,114 --> 00:18:51,411
Right.

286
00:18:51,482 --> 00:18:53,074
How did that go?

287
00:18:53,150 --> 00:18:55,118
It didn't change anything.

288
00:18:55,186 --> 00:18:57,086
What needed changing?

289
00:18:57,154 --> 00:19:01,215
I'd like to be more in control.

290
00:19:01,292 --> 00:19:02,919
Why?

291
00:19:02,993 --> 00:19:05,791
So people can quit
worrying about me.

292
00:19:06,864 --> 00:19:09,059
Well. I'll tell you something.

293
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:12,068
I'll be straight with you. Okay?

294
00:19:12,136 --> 00:19:14,866
I'm not big on control.

295
00:19:16,807 --> 00:19:18,775
But it's your money.

296
00:19:18,843 --> 00:19:20,708
So to speak.

297
00:19:21,846 --> 00:19:23,211
So to speak.

298
00:19:24,415 --> 00:19:26,484
Okay.

299
00:19:30,988 --> 00:19:33,582
How's Tuesdays...

300
00:19:33,657 --> 00:19:35,591
and Fridays. Same time?

301
00:19:35,659 --> 00:19:37,820
Twice a week?

302
00:19:37,895 --> 00:19:40,830
Well. Control's a tough nut.

303
00:19:40,898 --> 00:19:43,662
I've got swim practice every night.

304
00:19:45,169 --> 00:19:47,103
Well. That's a problem.

305
00:19:47,171 --> 00:19:50,572
How do we solve that?

306
00:19:51,609 --> 00:19:54,339
Guess I'll skip practice
twice a week.

307
00:19:54,411 --> 00:19:55,844
Well. It's up to you.

308
00:19:55,913 --> 00:19:58,347
I don't like being here.

309
00:19:58,415 --> 00:20:00,883
I don't like it at all.

310
00:20:02,319 --> 00:20:04,116
Mm-hmm.

311
00:20:06,323 --> 00:20:10,817
I saw Mort Swain.
His sister died.

312
00:20:10,895 --> 00:20:13,159
The one from Idaho?

313
00:20:13,230 --> 00:20:15,755
The one with the restaurant.

314
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:17,824
She died in Idaho?

315
00:20:17,902 --> 00:20:19,369
I guess so.

316
00:20:20,437 --> 00:20:21,768
Why?

317
00:20:21,839 --> 00:20:25,002
You said she was always traveling.

318
00:20:25,075 --> 00:20:26,508
I don't know.

319
00:20:26,577 --> 00:20:28,374
Maybe in Idaho.

320
00:20:28,445 --> 00:20:30,709
Maybe Kansas City.

321
00:20:37,187 --> 00:20:39,621
I went to see Dr. Berger.

322
00:20:39,690 --> 00:20:41,624
Berger?

323
00:20:41,692 --> 00:20:43,387
Yeah.

324
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:45,121
You didn't say anything. Good!

325
00:20:45,195 --> 00:20:46,787
I went today.

326
00:20:46,864 --> 00:20:49,799
I didn't know
you made an appointment.

327
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:51,129
How was it?

328
00:20:51,201 --> 00:20:52,862
It's a lot of money.

329
00:20:52,937 --> 00:20:54,871
It's okay.

330
00:20:54,939 --> 00:20:58,136
It's $50 an hour.
Twice a week.

331
00:20:58,208 --> 00:21:01,143
It's okay.
It is necessary.

332
00:21:01,211 --> 00:21:03,975
What did you talk about?

333
00:21:04,048 --> 00:21:05,242
Not much.

334
00:21:05,316 --> 00:21:06,749
What about your schedule?

335
00:21:06,817 --> 00:21:10,480
Well. It'll cut
into swim practice.

336
00:21:10,554 --> 00:21:12,647
Where's his office?

337
00:21:12,723 --> 00:21:14,156
Highland Park.

338
00:21:18,128 --> 00:21:20,096
Head straight!

339
00:21:20,164 --> 00:21:23,600
I don't want to tell you again.

340
00:21:25,336 --> 00:21:27,930
This is what I see.

341
00:21:28,005 --> 00:21:31,270
I see you yawning
and you coming late.

342
00:21:31,342 --> 00:21:34,072
I don't see you having fun.

343
00:21:34,144 --> 00:21:36,942
Are you getting enough sleep?

344
00:21:37,014 --> 00:21:38,413
Yeah.

345
00:21:39,950 --> 00:21:41,440
Are you having fun?

346
00:21:41,518 --> 00:21:42,780
Fun?

347
00:21:42,853 --> 00:21:46,380
There's no point
if you're not having fun.

348
00:21:46,457 --> 00:21:48,391
Yeah. I guess so.

349
00:21:48,459 --> 00:21:49,858
You guess so.

350
00:21:52,429 --> 00:21:54,420
Are you on medication?

351
00:21:54,498 --> 00:21:55,897
Tranquilizers?

352
00:21:55,966 --> 00:21:57,194
Anything?

353
00:21:57,267 --> 00:21:59,792
No. No. Sir.

354
00:21:59,870 --> 00:22:02,464
Did I ask you
if they gave you shock?

355
00:22:02,539 --> 00:22:04,029
Yeah.

356
00:22:04,108 --> 00:22:05,632
Yeah what?

357
00:22:05,709 --> 00:22:07,540
Yeah. You asked me.

358
00:22:07,611 --> 00:22:09,044
Yeah. They did.

359
00:22:11,315 --> 00:22:13,215
Don't look at us. Lazenby.

360
00:22:13,283 --> 00:22:15,217
Get in the water!

361
00:22:20,124 --> 00:22:23,457
I'm no doctor. Jarrett.

362
00:22:23,527 --> 00:22:27,258
I wouldn't let them
put electricity in my head.

363
00:22:29,366 --> 00:22:31,300
He drives me nuts!

364
00:22:31,368 --> 00:22:34,030
Everybody drives you nuts.

365
00:22:36,340 --> 00:22:38,274
Don and Fenetch looked good.

366
00:22:38,342 --> 00:22:40,207
They looked very good.

367
00:22:40,277 --> 00:22:43,212
Is he giving you a hard time?

368
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,214
Want a clarinet?

369
00:22:45,282 --> 00:22:47,216
Van Buren wants a clarinet.

370
00:22:47,284 --> 00:22:48,717
Who's selling it?

371
00:22:48,786 --> 00:22:50,720
My brother.
He needs a motorcycle.

372
00:22:50,788 --> 00:22:53,256
You stand behind me
in the choir.

373
00:22:53,323 --> 00:22:55,917
Oh. I do?
Is that you?

374
00:22:55,993 --> 00:22:58,359
You have a lot of energy.

375
00:22:58,429 --> 00:22:59,453
I do?

376
00:22:59,530 --> 00:23:01,259
I mean. That's good.

377
00:23:01,331 --> 00:23:03,265
My name's Jeannine Pratt.

378
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:04,766
Nice. Hi.

379
00:23:04,835 --> 00:23:06,268
You're Conrad Jarrett.

380
00:23:06,336 --> 00:23:07,496
Right.

381
00:23:09,673 --> 00:23:11,265
Yeah. Um. Bye.

382
00:23:11,341 --> 00:23:12,774
Bye-bye.

383
00:23:13,844 --> 00:23:16,779
"You've got a lot of energy."

384
00:23:20,184 --> 00:23:21,776
[Children]
Trick or treat!

385
00:23:21,852 --> 00:23:25,288
You're the scariest
ghost I've ever seen!

386
00:23:25,355 --> 00:23:26,788
You look wonderful.

387
00:23:26,857 --> 00:23:28,791
Thank you.

388
00:23:28,859 --> 00:23:29,791
There you go.

389
00:23:29,860 --> 00:23:31,293
Be careful.

390
00:23:31,361 --> 00:23:33,295
Thank you.
Good-bye.

391
00:23:34,364 --> 00:23:36,798
The Cabots.
Julie's first time.

392
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:38,801
She's so cute!

393
00:23:40,637 --> 00:23:43,197
Ha! Ha! Ha! Ha!

394
00:23:43,273 --> 00:23:46,470
Know what I've been thinking?

395
00:23:46,543 --> 00:23:48,477
That Christmas in London...

396
00:23:48,545 --> 00:23:51,981
would be like something
out of Dickens.

397
00:23:52,049 --> 00:23:54,483
We've never done that before.

398
00:23:54,551 --> 00:23:58,988
Maybe we shouldn't plan
to go away right now.

399
00:23:59,056 --> 00:24:00,990
We talked about it.

400
00:24:01,058 --> 00:24:02,992
We decided on that.

401
00:24:03,060 --> 00:24:04,994
Yeah. I know that.

402
00:24:05,062 --> 00:24:07,997
But the timing
doesn't seem right.

403
00:24:08,065 --> 00:24:11,000
We've always gone away
at Christmas.

404
00:24:11,068 --> 00:24:13,730
It'd be good for him. Too.

405
00:24:13,804 --> 00:24:16,238
Let's get back to normal.

406
00:24:16,306 --> 00:24:19,002
He's just started
with this doctor.

407
00:24:19,076 --> 00:24:21,010
He'll miss three weeks.

408
00:24:21,078 --> 00:24:22,511
Why interrupt it?

409
00:24:22,579 --> 00:24:25,514
Because I want to get away.

410
00:24:25,582 --> 00:24:28,517
I think we should.
It's important.

411
00:24:28,585 --> 00:24:33,022
Not if he doesn't
go through with this now.

412
00:24:33,090 --> 00:24:35,524
He might change his mind.

413
00:24:35,592 --> 00:24:38,026
If he changes his mind...

414
00:24:38,095 --> 00:24:40,290
it wasn't right for him.

415
00:24:40,364 --> 00:24:42,628
Does he want to go?

416
00:24:42,699 --> 00:24:45,634
He doesn't know what he wants.

417
00:26:52,829 --> 00:26:54,592
Ahh!

418
00:26:54,665 --> 00:26:56,360
Don't do that!

419
00:26:56,433 --> 00:26:57,866
I'm sorry.

420
00:26:57,935 --> 00:27:00,870
I didn't think you were here.

421
00:27:00,938 --> 00:27:02,872
I just got in.

422
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:04,874
No golf today.
Too cold.

423
00:27:04,942 --> 00:27:06,375
How was golf?

424
00:27:06,443 --> 00:27:07,876
I didn't play.

425
00:27:07,945 --> 00:27:09,378
It's colder today.

426
00:27:09,446 --> 00:27:12,882
I mean. For the year.
It's colder.

427
00:27:14,084 --> 00:27:15,517
Weren't you swimming?

428
00:27:15,585 --> 00:27:18,019
Yeah. Sorry I scared you.

429
00:27:18,088 --> 00:27:19,521
How'd it go?

430
00:27:19,589 --> 00:27:21,523
Good. I swam well.

431
00:27:21,591 --> 00:27:22,523
Good.

432
00:27:22,592 --> 00:27:26,028
I could swim the 50 if my...

433
00:27:26,096 --> 00:27:28,030
my timing got better.

434
00:27:28,098 --> 00:27:30,032
I'm a little off.

435
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:32,534
You must work at that.

436
00:27:32,602 --> 00:27:33,534
Yeah.

437
00:27:33,603 --> 00:27:37,641
I got 74 on a Trig quiz.

438
00:27:37,774 --> 00:27:39,173
74?

439
00:27:39,242 --> 00:27:42,177
Gee. I was awful at Trig.

440
00:27:42,245 --> 00:27:43,678
Oh. Yeah? Did you...

441
00:27:43,747 --> 00:27:45,908
You took Trig?

442
00:27:48,218 --> 00:27:49,845
Wait a minute.

443
00:27:52,255 --> 00:27:53,813
Did I take Trig?

444
00:27:57,494 --> 00:28:01,157
I bought you two shirts.
They're on your bed.

445
00:28:04,934 --> 00:28:06,765
Who'll be there?

446
00:28:06,836 --> 00:28:10,863
Well. The Murrays.
The Gunthers. And the Caines.

447
00:28:10,940 --> 00:28:13,738
Let's go to the movies instead.

448
00:28:13,810 --> 00:28:16,472
Don't be negative.

449
00:28:16,546 --> 00:28:18,878
That's not negative.
That's unpredictable.

450
00:28:18,948 --> 00:28:21,280
Let's go to the movies.

451
00:28:21,351 --> 00:28:22,750
Okay.

452
00:28:22,819 --> 00:28:24,377
Really?

453
00:28:24,454 --> 00:28:27,218
Okay. Yeah.
Come on. Let's go.

454
00:28:27,290 --> 00:28:28,723
What's our excuse?

455
00:28:29,793 --> 00:28:33,559
Beth wanted to go
to the movies.

456
00:28:33,630 --> 00:28:34,722
Good.

457
00:28:34,798 --> 00:28:36,322
Very good.

458
00:28:41,905 --> 00:28:43,839
All right now. Smile.

459
00:28:43,907 --> 00:28:46,774
Remember. Not too many martinis.

460
00:28:51,414 --> 00:28:54,850
Will you put that
with the others?

461
00:28:54,918 --> 00:28:56,852
Look. We're in time.

462
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,353
Look who's here!

463
00:28:58,421 --> 00:29:02,357
Three blocks away
and the last to arrive.

464
00:29:02,425 --> 00:29:03,858
Come on in.

465
00:29:03,927 --> 00:29:06,361
Happy birthday!
You look wonderful.

466
00:29:06,429 --> 00:29:07,862
Is that new?

467
00:29:07,931 --> 00:29:10,866
Yes. It is.
Do you like it?

468
00:29:11,935 --> 00:29:13,300
You did the mousse?

469
00:29:13,369 --> 00:29:14,666
It turned out well?

470
00:29:14,738 --> 00:29:17,298
Hey. Partner.
How are you?

471
00:29:17,373 --> 00:29:19,034
Hi there.

472
00:29:19,109 --> 00:29:21,009
Hi. Beth.

473
00:29:21,077 --> 00:29:22,601
Good to see you.

474
00:29:22,679 --> 00:29:24,010
Borrow the money.

475
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:25,513
I'll go public.

476
00:29:25,582 --> 00:29:29,678
I wouldn't do it now
because the market's low.

477
00:29:29,753 --> 00:29:31,516
Your hair looks wonderful.

478
00:29:31,588 --> 00:29:34,113
It's shorter. You like it?

479
00:29:34,190 --> 00:29:37,785
I said.
"Please put out your cigar."

480
00:29:37,861 --> 00:29:41,661
He says. "Huh?
I don't have another one."

481
00:29:42,866 --> 00:29:45,300
Good to see you!

482
00:29:45,368 --> 00:29:47,632
You look beautiful. As ever.

483
00:29:47,704 --> 00:29:49,137
In school...

484
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:54,302
they think they've got
to walk on the edge of danger.

485
00:29:54,377 --> 00:29:56,470
What are these hushed tones?

486
00:29:56,546 --> 00:29:58,605
He told the funniest joke!

487
00:30:00,884 --> 00:30:03,284
I'm not talking to you.

488
00:30:03,353 --> 00:30:04,650
Why?

489
00:30:04,721 --> 00:30:08,418
I have my fingers crossed
on this merger.

490
00:30:08,491 --> 00:30:09,651
Let's have lunch.

491
00:30:09,726 --> 00:30:11,990
I don't know my schedule.

492
00:30:12,061 --> 00:30:14,325
I'm free most days.

493
00:30:14,397 --> 00:30:16,991
Bob McLean's leaving
Coles and Johnson.

494
00:30:17,066 --> 00:30:19,000
Where is he going?

495
00:30:19,068 --> 00:30:21,036
He doesn't know.

496
00:30:21,104 --> 00:30:22,332
Jesus.

497
00:30:22,405 --> 00:30:23,872
No. You didn't.

498
00:30:23,940 --> 00:30:27,273
Isn't he the meanest man
you've met?

499
00:30:27,343 --> 00:30:29,641
When a ball is in play.

500
00:30:29,712 --> 00:30:33,671
If a player or caddy
accidentally move it...

501
00:30:33,750 --> 00:30:35,877
#Jolly good fellow #

