00:30:46,162 --> 00:30:48,687
# For #

506
00:30:48,765 --> 00:30:53,532
# Love ##

507
00:30:57,207 --> 00:31:00,370
Hi. Annie. What's your boy up to?

508
00:31:00,443 --> 00:31:01,876
Oh. Who knows?

509
00:31:01,945 --> 00:31:03,708
How's Conrad doing?

510
00:31:03,780 --> 00:31:05,714
He's great. Just great.

511
00:31:05,782 --> 00:31:09,980
I asked Donald.
He says they haven't talked much.

512
00:31:10,053 --> 00:31:12,715
I said maybe he's self-conscious.

513
00:31:12,789 --> 00:31:13,721
Oh!

514
00:31:17,126 --> 00:31:19,720
No. No. No.

515
00:31:19,796 --> 00:31:21,730
No. He's...

516
00:31:21,798 --> 00:31:25,325
There's a doctor
in Highland Park...

517
00:31:25,401 --> 00:31:27,733
that he sees twice a week.

518
00:31:27,804 --> 00:31:30,068
He's great. Just great.

519
00:31:30,139 --> 00:31:33,302
Is he still having some problems?

520
00:31:33,376 --> 00:31:35,241
No. Nothing like that.

521
00:31:35,311 --> 00:31:37,745
Just somebody to talk to...

522
00:31:37,814 --> 00:31:40,180
to polish off the rough edges.

523
00:31:40,250 --> 00:31:41,808
How are you. Darling?

524
00:31:41,885 --> 00:31:44,319
Is he falling asleep on you?

525
00:31:44,387 --> 00:31:46,116
Nah. He's great.

526
00:31:47,390 --> 00:31:49,187
[Mimicking "Mr. Wonderful"]
# Mr. Great. That's me #

527
00:31:54,264 --> 00:31:55,196
Hey.

528
00:31:56,900 --> 00:31:58,993
You drank too much.

529
00:31:59,068 --> 00:32:00,501
I'm not drunk.

530
00:32:00,570 --> 00:32:04,165
Why did you tell Annie
about Conrad's psychiatrist?

531
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,673
Why not?

532
00:32:05,742 --> 00:32:08,836
People don't hear
that thing easily.

533
00:32:08,912 --> 00:32:12,348
For most people.
It's a status symbol.

534
00:32:12,415 --> 00:32:14,849
Well. Your blurting it out...

535
00:32:14,918 --> 00:32:16,852
was a violation of privacy.

536
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,353
Whose privacy?

537
00:32:18,421 --> 00:32:20,252
The family's privacy!

538
00:32:20,323 --> 00:32:23,258
I think it is
a very private matter.

539
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,264
I tell you my dreams?

540
00:32:33,336 --> 00:32:35,770
I don't believe in dreams.

541
00:32:35,838 --> 00:32:39,296
What kind of
a psychiatrist are you?

542
00:32:39,375 --> 00:32:41,775
What's happening?

543
00:32:42,912 --> 00:32:44,209
What's going on?

544
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:46,214
I just feel...

545
00:32:46,282 --> 00:32:48,273
I feel so...

546
00:32:50,386 --> 00:32:51,318
What?

547
00:32:51,387 --> 00:32:53,184
Jumpy. I don't know.

548
00:32:53,256 --> 00:32:54,746
Look. Kiddo...

549
00:32:55,825 --> 00:32:57,417
I lied.

550
00:32:58,494 --> 00:33:00,428
I believe in dreams.

551
00:33:00,496 --> 00:33:04,432
Sometimes I want to know
what's happening when you're awake.

552
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:06,832
Something's making you nervous.

553
00:33:06,903 --> 00:33:09,371
Maybe I need a tranquilizer.

554
00:33:09,439 --> 00:33:10,531
Tranquilizer?

555
00:33:10,606 --> 00:33:12,904
What do you think?

556
00:33:12,976 --> 00:33:16,434
You look like something
out of The Body Snatchers.

557
00:33:16,512 --> 00:33:19,777
It's not my impression
that you need a tranquilizer.

558
00:33:21,684 --> 00:33:23,311
What is this?

559
00:33:23,386 --> 00:33:25,115
A clock.

560
00:33:25,188 --> 00:33:28,624
You can tell the time.
But I can't.

561
00:33:28,691 --> 00:33:31,819
So you know when
the hour's up?

562
00:33:31,894 --> 00:33:33,156
Right.

563
00:33:33,229 --> 00:33:34,856
50. 55 minutes?

