01:04:49,369 --> 01:04:50,802
What is wrong?

1127
01:04:50,871 --> 01:04:52,304
Ask him what's wrong.

1128
01:04:52,372 --> 01:04:56,103
Maybe you won't have to
hear it from Carol Lazenby.

1129
01:04:56,176 --> 01:04:57,575
Hear what?

1130
01:05:01,281 --> 01:05:03,749
I quit the swim team.

1131
01:05:03,817 --> 01:05:05,978
Carol thought I knew.

1132
01:05:06,053 --> 01:05:09,022
It happened over a month ago.

1133
01:05:09,089 --> 01:05:10,488
Quit? When?

1134
01:05:11,558 --> 01:05:14,220
Where have you been every night?

1135
01:05:14,294 --> 01:05:16,228
Nowhere.
The library mostly.

1136
01:05:16,296 --> 01:05:19,026
I didn't think it mattered.

1137
01:05:19,099 --> 01:05:21,533
That was meant for me.

1138
01:05:21,602 --> 01:05:24,833
It's important to hurt me. Right?

1139
01:05:24,905 --> 01:05:26,805
You have that backwards.

1140
01:05:26,874 --> 01:05:30,833
Do I embarrass you
in front of friends?

1141
01:05:30,911 --> 01:05:34,904
"Poor Beth believes
every lie her son tells."

1142
01:05:34,982 --> 01:05:36,472
I didn't lie.

1143
01:05:36,550 --> 01:05:40,577
You did when
you came home at 6:30!

1144
01:05:40,654 --> 01:05:44,715
If the lying's starting again.
I can't stand it!

1145
01:05:44,791 --> 01:05:47,055
Then go to Europe!

1146
01:05:47,127 --> 01:05:52,497
She only gives a fuck because
someone else knew about it first!

1147
01:05:52,566 --> 01:05:55,899
She never came
to the hospital...

1148
01:05:55,969 --> 01:05:59,496
because she's busy going
to goddamn Spain and Portugal!

1149
01:05:59,573 --> 01:06:04,067
She doesn't care if I'm hung up
by the balls out there.

1150
01:06:04,144 --> 01:06:06,942
They may talk like this
at the hospital...

1151
01:06:07,014 --> 01:06:09,539
but we're not at the hospital.

1152
01:06:09,616 --> 01:06:12,050
You never came to the hospital!

1153
01:06:12,119 --> 01:06:14,815
She had the flu
and couldn't come inside.

1154
01:06:14,888 --> 01:06:17,857
She would've visited Buck
in the hospital!

1155
01:06:17,925 --> 01:06:20,826
Buck never would've been
in the hospital!

1156
01:06:20,894 --> 01:06:22,555
That is enough!

1157
01:06:22,629 --> 01:06:25,359
I won't do it again.

1158
01:06:25,432 --> 01:06:28,026
What in hell has happened?

1159
01:06:28,101 --> 01:06:30,626
Somebody better go up there.

1160
01:06:30,704 --> 01:06:33,070
He walks all over us...

1161
01:06:33,140 --> 01:06:36,303
then you apologize to him.

1162
01:06:36,376 --> 01:06:38,105
You've been apologizing to him...

1163
01:06:38,178 --> 01:06:41,272
since he returned from the hospital!

1164
01:06:41,348 --> 01:06:44,806
I'm trying to
goddamn understand him!

1165
01:06:44,885 --> 01:06:46,512
Don't talk to me...

1166
01:06:46,586 --> 01:06:49,146
the way he talks to you.

1167
01:06:49,222 --> 01:06:51,690
Let's not fight. Okay?

1168
01:06:51,758 --> 01:06:53,316
No fighting. Okay?

1169
01:06:53,393 --> 01:06:55,293
Please.

1170
01:06:55,362 --> 01:06:56,989
Let's go upstairs.

1171
01:07:16,116 --> 01:07:18,516
I want to talk to you.

1172
01:07:18,585 --> 01:07:21,145
I didn't mean any of it.

1173
01:07:21,221 --> 01:07:23,416
Please don't be mad.

1174
01:07:23,490 --> 01:07:26,357
I'm trying to
understand what happened.

1175
01:07:26,426 --> 01:07:28,917
I don't know what happened.

1176
01:07:28,996 --> 01:07:30,930
I didn't mean it.

1177
01:07:30,998 --> 01:07:34,161
Tell her I'm sorry. Will you?

1178
01:07:34,234 --> 01:07:35,326
Why don't you?

1179
01:07:35,402 --> 01:07:37,165
God. I can't!

1180
01:07:37,237 --> 01:07:39,705
I can't talk to her!

1181
01:07:39,773 --> 01:07:41,240
Why not?

1182
01:07:41,308 --> 01:07:43,299
It doesn't change anything.

1183
01:07:43,377 --> 01:07:47,905
It doesn't change
the way she looks at me.

1184
01:07:47,981 --> 01:07:52,008
She was hurt because
you quit the team.

1185
01:07:52,085 --> 01:07:54,553
I don't mean just now.

1186
01:07:54,621 --> 01:07:57,112
I don't mean just today.

1187
01:07:57,190 --> 01:07:59,181
Explain it to me.

1188
01:07:59,259 --> 01:08:02,251
I can't. You don't see things.

1189
01:08:02,329 --> 01:08:03,796
What things?

1190
01:08:03,864 --> 01:08:05,491
What things?

1191
01:08:05,565 --> 01:08:08,557
I want you to tell me.

1192
01:08:08,635 --> 01:08:11,729
Can't you see she hates me?

1193
01:08:11,805 --> 01:08:13,705
She doesn't hate you.

1194
01:08:13,774 --> 01:08:16,299
You're right.
She doesn't.

1195
01:08:16,376 --> 01:08:18,367
Please leave me alone.

1196
01:08:31,191 --> 01:08:34,649
Do you think Dr. Berger's helping you?

1197
01:08:34,728 --> 01:08:36,593
It's not his fault.

1198
01:08:42,736 --> 01:08:45,705
I'll be downstairs if you need me.

1199
01:08:50,143 --> 01:08:54,136
Tuesday everything was hunky-dory.

1200
01:08:54,214 --> 01:08:55,647
You're the doctor.

1201
01:08:58,652 --> 01:09:01,587
Don't take refuge
in one-liners. Okay?

1202
01:09:01,655 --> 01:09:03,589
Because that pisses me off.

1203
01:09:03,657 --> 01:09:06,091
Okay. Okay.

1204
01:09:06,159 --> 01:09:07,592
Everything was fine...

1205
01:09:07,661 --> 01:09:10,596
till you had the fight
with your mother?

1206
01:09:10,664 --> 01:09:12,097
I don't blame her.

1207
01:09:12,165 --> 01:09:14,599
She's got her reasons.
It's impossible...

1208
01:09:14,668 --> 01:09:16,602
after all the shit I've pulled.

1209
01:09:16,670 --> 01:09:18,604
What shit have you pulled?

1210
01:09:21,174 --> 01:09:23,540
I'm talking about proportion.

1211
01:09:23,610 --> 01:09:25,510
Now. What shit?

1212
01:09:28,582 --> 01:09:32,541
You can find one example.

1213
01:09:32,619 --> 01:09:34,553
Don't say you tried suicide.

1214
01:09:34,621 --> 01:09:36,555
What have you done lately?

1215
01:09:36,623 --> 01:09:40,252
I'll never be forgiven for that.

1216
01:09:40,327 --> 01:09:41,817
Never.

1217
01:09:41,895 --> 01:09:45,991
You can't get out
the blood in her towels...

1218
01:09:46,066 --> 01:09:48,091
and in her rug.

1219
01:09:48,168 --> 01:09:50,693
Everything
had to be pitched.

1220
01:09:50,770 --> 01:09:54,365
The bathroom tile
had to be regrouted.

1221
01:09:54,441 --> 01:09:56,170
She fired the maid...

1222
01:09:56,243 --> 01:09:59,076
because she couldn't dust right.

1223
01:09:59,146 --> 01:10:01,671
If you think I'll forgive...

1224
01:10:01,748 --> 01:10:03,238
she's gonna forgive me...

1225
01:10:11,258 --> 01:10:12,418
What?

1226
01:10:32,512 --> 01:10:36,278
I think I just figured
something out.

1227
01:10:36,349 --> 01:10:37,816
What?

1228
01:10:39,419 --> 01:10:41,853
Who it is who can't forgive who.

1229
01:10:47,127 --> 01:10:50,563
[Berger]
A real problem has a real solution.

1230
01:10:50,630 --> 01:10:52,621
[Conrad]
I've heard this before.

1231
01:10:52,699 --> 01:10:55,725
Doesn't make it any less true.

1232
01:10:55,802 --> 01:10:57,292
I'm so tired.

1233
01:10:57,371 --> 01:11:00,397
That's some secret
you've been keeping.

1234
01:11:00,474 --> 01:11:03,500
So what do I do now?

1235
01:11:05,112 --> 01:11:07,137
Recognize her limitations.

1236
01:11:08,248 --> 01:11:10,739
Like she can't love me.

1237
01:11:10,817 --> 01:11:14,753
No. Like she can't
love you enough.

1238
01:11:14,821 --> 01:11:17,984
Don't blame her
for not loving you...

1239
01:11:18,058 --> 01:11:20,049
more than she's able.

1240
01:11:20,127 --> 01:11:22,118
She loves my father.

1241
01:11:22,195 --> 01:11:24,186
She loved my brother.

1242
01:11:24,264 --> 01:11:25,925
It's me.

1243
01:11:25,999 --> 01:11:29,093
We're back to
the rotten kid routine.

1244
01:11:29,169 --> 01:11:33,003
She can't love you
because you're unlovable.

1245
01:11:33,073 --> 01:11:36,167
How come your Dad loves you?

1246
01:11:36,243 --> 01:11:38,711
He feels responsible.

1247
01:11:38,779 --> 01:11:40,770
Besides. He loves everybody.

1248
01:11:40,847 --> 01:11:43,372
The guy's got no taste.

1249
01:11:43,450 --> 01:11:46,442
He loves you. But he's wrong.

1250
01:11:46,520 --> 01:11:47,987
Look...

1251
01:11:48,055 --> 01:11:51,047
maybe she can't express it...

1252
01:11:51,124 --> 01:11:53,092
the way you'd like.

1253
01:11:53,160 --> 01:11:56,425
Maybe she's afraid
to show her feelings.

1254
01:11:56,496 --> 01:11:58,726
What do you mean?

1255
01:11:58,799 --> 01:12:01,131
There's someone
besides your mother...

1256
01:12:01,201 --> 01:12:02,793
you've got to forgive.

1257
01:12:02,869 --> 01:12:04,632
You mean me?

1258
01:12:06,506 --> 01:12:09,031
For trying to off myself?

1259
01:12:11,178 --> 01:12:13,169
Don't stare.
What for?

1260
01:12:13,246 --> 01:12:17,182
Why don't you let yourself
off the hook?

1261
01:12:17,250 --> 01:12:20,276
What did I do?

1262
01:12:20,353 --> 01:12:21,945
What did I do?

1263
01:12:22,022 --> 01:12:23,489
We'll talk Thursday.

1264
01:12:23,557 --> 01:12:24,489
Come on!

1265
01:12:24,558 --> 01:12:26,287
Time's up.

1266
01:12:26,359 --> 01:12:28,793
What did I do?

1267
01:12:28,862 --> 01:12:30,261
You know the rules.

1268
01:12:30,330 --> 01:12:31,820
What rules?

1269
01:12:31,898 --> 01:12:33,593
Think about it.

1270
01:12:33,667 --> 01:12:35,259
Just think about it.

1271
01:12:38,405 --> 01:12:39,667
Jesus!

1272
01:12:43,877 --> 01:12:46,437
Say. After going to a new high...

1273
01:12:46,513 --> 01:12:48,879
it falls to 1121/4...

1274
01:12:48,949 --> 01:12:51,941
and then rallies on good volume.

1275
01:12:52,018 --> 01:12:54,452
I order to buy 4.000.

1276
01:12:54,521 --> 01:12:58,787
If I get the 4.000 at 1133/4.
I know something's wrong.

1277
01:12:58,859 --> 01:13:02,795
But suppose I order
to buy the 4.000 shares...

1278
01:13:02,863 --> 01:13:05,730
and I plug in at 1133/4...

1279
01:13:05,799 --> 01:13:09,667
I get 2.000 at 114.
500 at 1141/4...

1280
01:13:09,736 --> 01:13:12,603
and the rest on the way up.

1281
01:13:12,672 --> 01:13:14,697
Then I know I'm right.

1282
01:13:14,774 --> 01:13:17,641
I'm going to peel off here.

1283
01:13:17,711 --> 01:13:19,645
See you later.

1284
01:13:24,384 --> 01:13:27,012
[Voice Echoing]
Suppose the order to buy...

1285
01:13:27,087 --> 01:13:29,021
[Beth's Voice]
You let him walk all over us...

1286
01:13:29,089 --> 01:13:30,351
and you apologize.

1287
01:13:30,423 --> 01:13:32,084
[Man's Voice]
500 at 114...

1288
01:13:32,159 --> 01:13:34,127
[Conrad's Voice]
Dad, you don't see things.

1289
01:13:34,194 --> 01:13:35,991
[Beth]
You've been apologizing...

1290
01:13:36,062 --> 01:13:39,361
since he returned from the hospital.

1291
01:13:39,432 --> 01:13:41,366
Tell her to stop it!

1292
01:13:41,434 --> 01:13:44,494
Buck never would've
been in the hospital!

1293
01:13:44,571 --> 01:13:45,902
She hates me!

1294
01:14:08,195 --> 01:14:09,924
I want to be clear.

1295
01:14:09,996 --> 01:14:11,793
That's good.

1296
01:14:13,700 --> 01:14:18,296
In the car.
I was thinking. "be clear."

1297
01:14:21,708 --> 01:14:24,142
I suppose that's what
psychiatry's about.

1298
01:14:24,211 --> 01:14:26,611
Being precise and clear.

1299
01:14:26,680 --> 01:14:28,648
And honest, of course.

1300
01:14:30,050 --> 01:14:34,009
I'm not a great believer
in psychiatry.

1301
01:14:34,087 --> 01:14:35,816
Okay.

1302
01:14:35,889 --> 01:14:39,518
What happens here
is between you and him...

1303
01:14:39,593 --> 01:14:41,584
and I respect that.

1304
01:14:41,661 --> 01:14:44,095
He's better.
I can see that.

1305
01:14:44,164 --> 01:14:46,962
I just don't believe in psychiatry...

1306
01:14:47,033 --> 01:14:50,298
as a panacea for everybody.

1307
01:14:50,370 --> 01:14:51,837
Neither do I.

1308
01:14:54,808 --> 01:14:59,370
I wish I knew what
I was doing here.

1309
01:14:59,446 --> 01:15:03,405
You said you could shed
some light on some things.

1310
01:15:03,483 --> 01:15:07,044
I meant in terms of Conrad.

1311
01:15:07,120 --> 01:15:09,611
I knew something was wrong...

1312
01:15:09,689 --> 01:15:12,180
even before he tried suicide.

1313
01:15:12,259 --> 01:15:14,227
But I thought that...

1314
01:15:15,328 --> 01:15:18,320
It's clear that he's very smart.

1315
01:15:18,398 --> 01:15:21,390
He's always been
an "A" student.

1316
01:15:21,468 --> 01:15:23,959
Naturally. I thought
intelligent people...

1317
01:15:24,037 --> 01:15:26,437
could work out their problems.

1318
01:15:26,506 --> 01:15:29,100
But you still feel responsible?

1319
01:15:29,175 --> 01:15:31,200
Yeah, sure I do.

1320
01:15:31,278 --> 01:15:33,303
It's hard not to.

1321
01:15:33,380 --> 01:15:37,942
It was just luck that
I happened to be there...

1322
01:15:38,018 --> 01:15:39,986
when he tried it.

1323
01:15:40,053 --> 01:15:42,749
We both could've been away.

1324
01:15:42,822 --> 01:15:46,815
You think of yourself
as a lucky man?

1325
01:15:46,893 --> 01:15:48,383
No. No. No.

1326
01:15:48,461 --> 01:15:53,489
I used to think that
I was a lucky person...

1327
01:15:53,566 --> 01:15:55,227
before the accident.

1328
01:15:59,906 --> 01:16:02,932
I guess the whole of life...

1329
01:16:03,009 --> 01:16:05,477
is nothing but an accident...

1330
01:16:05,545 --> 01:16:07,410
what happens to you.

1331
01:16:07,480 --> 01:16:10,415
That sounds like
the philosophy of a drifter.

1332
01:16:10,483 --> 01:16:12,314
Yeah. Maybe.

1333
01:16:12,385 --> 01:16:14,717
Maybe I am drifting a little.

1334
01:16:14,788 --> 01:16:18,315
I can see the two of them...

1335
01:16:18,391 --> 01:16:20,382
drifting away from me...

1336
01:16:20,460 --> 01:16:22,985
and I just stand watching.

1337
01:16:23,063 --> 01:16:27,227
What would you want
to do about that?

1338
01:16:27,300 --> 01:16:29,791
Something.
I don't know what.

1339
01:16:29,869 --> 01:16:33,327
I feel like
I'm sitting on a fence.

1340
01:16:33,406 --> 01:16:36,432
They're on opposite sides
of this fence?

1341
01:16:36,509 --> 01:16:39,239
Yeah... No.

1342
01:16:39,312 --> 01:16:40,506
I don't know.

1343
01:16:40,580 --> 01:16:45,142
I see her not being able
to forgive him.

1344
01:16:46,219 --> 01:16:47,743
For what?

1345
01:16:47,821 --> 01:16:49,755
I don't know exactly.

1346
01:16:49,823 --> 01:16:52,314
Being too much like her.

1347
01:16:52,392 --> 01:16:57,420
People always think that
she and Buck are... were alike.

1348
01:16:58,531 --> 01:17:01,523
But it's really she and Conrad.

1349
01:17:01,601 --> 01:17:04,092
They were the only two...

1350
01:17:04,170 --> 01:17:07,162
that didn't cry at the funeral.

1351
01:17:07,240 --> 01:17:11,267
It's not easy for me to admit this...

1352
01:17:11,344 --> 01:17:12,811
but. Um...

1353
01:17:12,879 --> 01:17:14,346
she didn't...

1354
01:17:18,351 --> 01:17:21,878
His mother doesn't
show him much affection.

1355
01:17:21,955 --> 01:17:25,618
I'm not trying
to put her down.

1356
01:17:25,692 --> 01:17:29,219
Did she give Buck
much affection?

1357
01:17:29,295 --> 01:17:31,729
God. Yes.
She loved Buck.

1358
01:17:31,798 --> 01:17:33,766
Bucky got so much.

1359
01:17:33,833 --> 01:17:37,360
What she felt for him was special.

1360
01:17:37,437 --> 01:17:39,962
He was her first-born.

1361
01:17:40,039 --> 01:17:41,802
And you?

1362
01:17:41,875 --> 01:17:43,342
I loved Buck.

1363
01:17:43,410 --> 01:17:45,571
I mean your wife's affection.

1364
01:17:45,645 --> 01:17:47,112
For me?

1365
01:17:47,180 --> 01:17:48,477
Yes.

1366
01:17:49,582 --> 01:17:51,345
She's very...

1367
01:17:51,418 --> 01:17:55,514
No. There's no problem
with her for me.

1368
01:17:55,588 --> 01:17:59,285
We've been married
nearly 21 years.

1369
01:18:00,393 --> 01:18:01,860
Everybody loves Beth.

1370
01:18:01,928 --> 01:18:05,329
For Conrad. It's been difficult.

1371
01:18:05,398 --> 01:18:08,196
He didn't talk about that?

1372
01:18:08,268 --> 01:18:11,260
We don't know what happens here.

1373
01:18:11,337 --> 01:18:13,305
It doesn't come up.

1374
01:18:17,777 --> 01:18:20,746
I guess that's what it is.

1375
01:18:20,814 --> 01:18:23,146
It's private here. Isn't it?

1376
01:18:23,216 --> 01:18:24,649
Mm-hmm.
Very private.

1377
01:18:28,421 --> 01:18:32,357
I think I know why I came here.

1378
01:18:34,461 --> 01:18:37,794
I think I came here
to talk about myself.

1379
01:18:37,864 --> 01:18:40,628
Okay. Why don't we?

1380
01:18:47,140 --> 01:18:48,475
Hi.

1381
01:18:48,608 --> 01:18:52,545
[Car Buzzer Alarm]

1382
01:18:52,545 --> 01:18:53,512
Calvin?

1383
01:18:54,714 --> 01:18:56,579
[Buzzing Continues]

1384
01:18:56,649 --> 01:18:58,116
What's the matter?

1385
01:19:04,257 --> 01:19:06,748
This will sound strange.

1386
01:19:08,328 --> 01:19:12,321
What I'm going to say
will sound strange.

1387
01:19:12,398 --> 01:19:13,865
What happened?

1388
01:19:13,933 --> 01:19:15,366
Come inside.

1389
01:19:16,703 --> 01:19:19,467
Could we talk about
Buck's funeral?

1390
01:19:19,539 --> 01:19:21,131
What?

1391
