Everything will be okay!

1664
01:37:39,103 --> 01:37:40,400
Hang on. Brother!

1665
01:37:40,471 --> 01:37:41,995
Don't let go!

1666
01:37:42,073 --> 01:37:43,631
Stay with me!

1667
01:37:43,708 --> 01:37:45,232
Stay with me!

1668
01:37:45,310 --> 01:37:48,108
Stay with me!

1669
01:37:52,250 --> 01:37:53,512
Oh. God!

1670
01:37:56,988 --> 01:37:58,216
Bucky!

1671
01:37:59,624 --> 01:38:00,716
Buck!

1672
01:38:02,026 --> 01:38:03,857
Buck!

1673
01:38:08,633 --> 01:38:09,622
[Berger]
Hello.

1674
01:38:09,701 --> 01:38:11,259
This is Conrad.

1675
01:38:11,336 --> 01:38:12,769
What's going on?

1676
01:38:12,837 --> 01:38:14,805
I need to see you.

1677
01:38:14,872 --> 01:38:16,339
Where are you?

1678
01:38:16,407 --> 01:38:17,965
I don't know.

1679
01:38:18,042 --> 01:38:19,475
All right.

1680
01:38:19,544 --> 01:38:21,512
Get to the office.

1681
01:38:21,579 --> 01:38:23,012
I'll meet you there.

1682
01:38:23,081 --> 01:38:24,309
Okay.

1683
01:38:28,519 --> 01:38:31,010
Good. You're here.

1684
01:38:31,089 --> 01:38:32,522
Something happened.

1685
01:38:32,590 --> 01:38:34,057
Just a minute.

1686
01:38:34,125 --> 01:38:36,593
Wait till we get inside.

1687
01:38:38,763 --> 01:38:39,695
There.

1688
01:38:41,265 --> 01:38:42,823
Shit.

1689
01:38:42,900 --> 01:38:46,597
You'd think they'd assume
there'd be emergencies.

1690
01:38:46,671 --> 01:38:48,536
Don't take it off.
Just sit down.

1691
01:38:53,277 --> 01:38:54,209
Something happened.

1692
01:38:54,278 --> 01:38:55,336
What?

1693
01:38:55,413 --> 01:38:56,812
It's...

1694
01:38:56,881 --> 01:38:58,280
It's what?

1695
01:38:58,349 --> 01:38:59,816
Oh. God!

1696
01:39:01,419 --> 01:39:02,943
I need something.

1697
01:39:03,021 --> 01:39:04,147
What?

1698
01:39:04,222 --> 01:39:05,712
It keeps coming.

1699
01:39:05,790 --> 01:39:07,690
I can't stop it!

1700
01:39:07,759 --> 01:39:09,351
Don't try.

1701
01:39:09,427 --> 01:39:11,952
Got to get off the hook.

1702
01:39:12,030 --> 01:39:13,657
For what?

1703
01:39:13,731 --> 01:39:15,790
What I did to him!

1704
01:39:15,867 --> 01:39:16,993
What?

1705
01:39:17,068 --> 01:39:19,536
It must be somebody's fault...

1706
01:39:19,604 --> 01:39:21,765
or there's no point!

1707
01:39:21,839 --> 01:39:23,830
What point? It happened!

1708
01:39:23,908 --> 01:39:26,968
Oh. No. I don't mean that.

1709
01:39:27,045 --> 01:39:28,535
It's just that...

1710
01:39:28,613 --> 01:39:31,138
Bucky. I didn't mean it.

1711
01:39:31,215 --> 01:39:34,184
Bucky, I didn't mean it.

1712
01:39:34,252 --> 01:39:36,083
Bucky!

1713
01:39:36,154 --> 01:39:37,178
It wasn't your fault.

1714
01:39:37,255 --> 01:39:39,553
You said. "Get the sail down!"

1715
01:39:39,624 --> 01:39:41,751
I couldn't! It jammed!

1716
01:39:41,826 --> 01:39:43,521
And then the halyard jammed!

1717
01:39:43,594 --> 01:39:45,528
Because the goddamned
halyard jammed!

1718
01:39:45,596 --> 01:39:48,531
Then you're sittin' here
screwing around!

1719
01:39:48,599 --> 01:39:50,328
Until it's too late!

1720
01:39:50,401 --> 01:39:53,564
And I'm supposed
to take care of it!

1721
01:39:53,638 --> 01:39:54,832
That wasn't fair.

1722
01:39:54,906 --> 01:39:57,841
No! And then
you say. "Hang on!"

1723
01:39:57,909 --> 01:39:59,001
"Hang on!"

1724
01:39:59,077 --> 01:40:00,704
Then you let go!

1725
01:40:00,778 --> 01:40:02,336
Why'd you let go?

1726
01:40:02,413 --> 01:40:03,641
I got tired!

1727
01:40:03,714 --> 01:40:06,342
Yeah? Well. Screw you. You jerk!

1728
01:40:18,830 --> 01:40:22,231
It hurts to be mad at him.

1729
01:40:22,300 --> 01:40:23,767
Yeah.

1730
01:40:26,037 --> 01:40:28,062
He just wasn't careful.

1731
01:40:28,139 --> 01:40:32,041
He didn't see how
a bad thing might happen.

1732
01:40:32,110 --> 01:40:35,876
Bad things happen even
when people are careful.

1733
01:40:35,947 --> 01:40:37,881
We should've come in...

1734
01:40:37,949 --> 01:40:40,543
when it started to look bad.

1735
01:40:40,618 --> 01:40:42,950
So you made a mistake.

1736
01:40:43,020 --> 01:40:45,318
Why did he let go?

1737
01:40:45,389 --> 01:40:46,879
Why?

1738
01:40:46,958 --> 01:40:50,018
Maybe you were stronger.

1739
01:40:50,094 --> 01:40:53,325
Did that ever occur to you?

1740
01:41:01,272 --> 01:41:04,264
How long will you
punish yourself?

1741
01:41:04,342 --> 01:41:05,468
When will you quit?

1742
01:41:05,543 --> 01:41:07,238
I'd like to.

1743
01:41:07,311 --> 01:41:08,642
Why don't you?

1744
01:41:08,713 --> 01:41:11,443
It's not that easy.

1745
01:41:18,022 --> 01:41:19,489
God...

1746
01:41:19,557 --> 01:41:21,525
I loved him.

1747
01:41:25,663 --> 01:41:27,654
I know.

1748
01:41:42,180 --> 01:41:45,377
What happened?
What started all this?

1749
01:41:45,449 --> 01:41:46,939
Karen.

1750
01:41:48,719 --> 01:41:51,017
She killed herself.

1751
01:41:51,088 --> 01:41:54,114
I just found out she's dead.

1752
01:41:54,192 --> 01:41:56,251
Jesus.

1753
01:41:56,327 --> 01:41:58,522
She was fine.

1754
01:41:58,596 --> 01:42:00,928
No. She wasn't.

1755
01:42:00,998 --> 01:42:04,490
She told me!
She said she was...

1756
01:42:04,569 --> 01:42:05,536
What?

1757
01:42:05,603 --> 01:42:08,367
She was busy and
feeling good and...

1758
01:42:08,439 --> 01:42:09,463
What?

1759
01:42:11,242 --> 01:42:12,436
What?

1760
01:42:12,510 --> 01:42:13,909
If I'd known...

1761
01:42:13,978 --> 01:42:15,468
I could've done something.

1762
01:42:15,546 --> 01:42:18,344
You're taking her on. Too?

1763
01:42:18,416 --> 01:42:19,348
No!

1764
01:42:19,417 --> 01:42:20,349
No?

1765
01:42:20,418 --> 01:42:21,885
No. I just...

1766
01:42:21,953 --> 01:42:22,885
What?

1767
01:42:22,954 --> 01:42:24,387
That isn't it.

1768
01:42:24,455 --> 01:42:27,549
I feel really bad about this.

1769
01:42:27,625 --> 01:42:30,958
Just let me feel bad about this!

1770
01:42:32,129 --> 01:42:33,426
Okay.

1771
01:42:35,733 --> 01:42:38,998
Listen. I feel
bad about it. Too.

1772
01:42:43,040 --> 01:42:45,565
Why do things
happen to people?

1773
01:42:45,643 --> 01:42:48,043
It isn't fair.

1774
01:42:48,112 --> 01:42:50,808
You're right.
It isn't fair.

1775
01:42:50,881 --> 01:42:53,281
You just do one wrong thing...

1776
01:42:53,351 --> 01:42:54,818
and...

1777
01:42:54,885 --> 01:42:57,479
Um-hmm.

1778
01:42:57,555 --> 01:43:01,389
And what was the one
wrong thing you did?

1779
01:43:08,365 --> 01:43:09,832
You know.

1780
01:43:22,846 --> 01:43:24,609
You know.

1781
01:43:27,618 --> 01:43:29,518
I hung on.

1782
01:43:29,586 --> 01:43:32,714
I stayed with the boat.

1783
01:43:32,790 --> 01:43:34,417
Exactly.

1784
01:43:40,130 --> 01:43:44,123
Now. You can live
with that. Can't you?

1785
01:43:50,274 --> 01:43:52,242
I'm scared!

1786
01:43:52,309 --> 01:43:54,504
I'm scared.

1787
01:43:54,578 --> 01:43:56,808
Feelings are scary.

1788
01:43:56,880 --> 01:43:58,973
And sometimes they're painful.

1789
01:43:59,049 --> 01:44:01,313
If you can't feel pain...

1790
01:44:01,385 --> 01:44:04,377
you won't feel
anything else.

1791
01:44:04,455 --> 01:44:07,049
You know what I'm saying?

1792
01:44:10,160 --> 01:44:11,718
I think so.

1793
01:44:14,665 --> 01:44:16,394
You're here. You're alive.

1794
01:44:16,467 --> 01:44:19,265
Don't say you don't feel that.

1795
01:44:19,336 --> 01:44:21,566
It doesn't feel good.

1796
01:44:21,638 --> 01:44:23,071
It is good.

1797
01:44:23,140 --> 01:44:24,607
Believe me.

1798
01:44:29,013 --> 01:44:30,878
How do you know?

1799
01:44:32,950 --> 01:44:35,145
Because I'm your friend.

1800
01:44:39,456 --> 01:44:42,892
I don't know
what I would've done...

1801
01:44:42,960 --> 01:44:45,394
if you hadn't been here.

1802
01:44:48,966 --> 01:44:51,696
You're really my friend?

1803
01:44:53,804 --> 01:44:56,602
I am. Count on it.

1804
01:45:49,359 --> 01:45:50,792
Hi.

1805
01:45:50,861 --> 01:45:52,294
I would've called...

1806
01:45:52,362 --> 01:45:55,297
but I didn't
want to wake anyone.

1807
01:45:55,365 --> 01:45:56,798
About the other night...

1808
01:45:56,867 --> 01:45:59,301
I liked being with you.

1809
01:45:59,369 --> 01:46:01,803
I didn't like myself.

1810
01:46:01,872 --> 01:46:03,806
Conrad. I was stupid.

1811
01:46:03,874 --> 01:46:06,809
That was dumb of me to laugh.

1812
01:46:06,877 --> 01:46:08,811
It was my fault.

1813
01:46:08,879 --> 01:46:10,904
I was embarrassed.

1814
01:46:10,981 --> 01:46:12,141
Really?

1815
01:46:12,216 --> 01:46:13,979
You were embarrassed?

1816
01:46:14,051 --> 01:46:16,281
When those boys came in...

1817
01:46:16,353 --> 01:46:18,844
it was awful and awkward.

1818
01:46:18,922 --> 01:46:21,186
When I'm embarrassed. I laugh.

1819
01:46:21,258 --> 01:46:24,557
They were just having
a good time.

1820
01:46:24,628 --> 01:46:28,587
I let them interfere
with what was happening.

1821
01:46:28,665 --> 01:46:30,132
It was dumb.

1822
01:46:30,200 --> 01:46:33,727
I've done lots of
dumb things lately.

1823
01:46:33,804 --> 01:46:38,503
I just didn't know if you were
being straight with me.

1824
01:46:41,645 --> 01:46:43,112
Yeah?

1825
01:46:43,180 --> 01:46:46,547
Anyway. I'd like
to try it again.

1826
01:46:46,617 --> 01:46:48,050
It worked okay...

1827
01:46:48,118 --> 01:46:50,245
except for the bowling.

1828
01:46:50,320 --> 01:46:51,787
Yes.

1829
01:46:51,855 --> 01:46:53,720
Yes?

1830
01:46:54,825 --> 01:46:56,884
Yes.

1831
01:46:57,961 --> 01:47:00,452
Are you going to school?

1832
01:47:00,531 --> 01:47:03,364
No. Not on Sunday.

1833
01:47:06,203 --> 01:47:08,194
Have you eaten?

1834
01:47:08,272 --> 01:47:10,297
No. I haven't.

1835
01:47:10,374 --> 01:47:12,808
Do you want some breakfast?

1836
01:47:14,745 --> 01:47:16,212
Okay.

1837
01:47:29,960 --> 01:47:31,257
Mom!

1838
01:47:33,130 --> 01:47:35,496
All right.
How about that?

1839
01:47:35,566 --> 01:47:36,999
Boy. Oh. Boy.

1840
01:47:37,067 --> 01:47:39,035
I do love that.

1841
01:47:39,102 --> 01:47:42,094
These holes sure do love you.

1842
01:47:42,172 --> 01:47:46,165
We should spend more time
playing golf together.

1843
01:47:46,243 --> 01:47:49,212
Maybe our next vacation...
strictly golf.

1844
01:47:49,279 --> 01:47:50,746
Pinehurst.
Myrtle Beach.

1845
01:47:50,814 --> 01:47:52,782
Pinehurst would be nice.

1846
01:47:52,849 --> 01:47:55,841
I think Connie would
like Pinehurst.

1847
01:47:55,919 --> 01:47:59,377
Is that deliberate
or just a reflex?

1848
01:47:59,456 --> 01:48:02,448
I assumed you meant him. Too.

1849
01:48:02,526 --> 01:48:05,495
I'm surprised you
haven't called him.

1850
01:48:05,562 --> 01:48:07,530
I'll call him tonight.

1851
01:48:07,598 --> 01:48:10,590
Can we have a little drink?

1852
01:48:10,667 --> 01:48:12,635
Drink. Yes. Little. No.

1853
01:48:12,703 --> 01:48:14,170
Let's finish this.

1854
01:48:14,238 --> 01:48:15,170
What?

1855
01:48:15,239 --> 01:48:16,706
What you started.

1856
01:48:16,773 --> 01:48:18,741
Me? There's no point.

1857
01:48:18,809 --> 01:48:20,276
He controls you.

1858
01:48:20,344 --> 01:48:22,312
He isn't the problem.

1859
01:48:22,379 --> 01:48:23,846
Isn't he?

1860
01:48:23,914 --> 01:48:27,315
No. Let's talk about
what's bothering you.

1861
01:48:27,384 --> 01:48:30,376
No. Let's discuss
what's bothering you.

1862
01:48:30,454 --> 01:48:34,447
How did I make you
so angry with me?

1863
01:48:34,524 --> 01:48:36,992
You blame me
for everything.

1864
01:48:37,060 --> 01:48:39,528
Can't you see
beyond yourself?

1865
01:48:39,596 --> 01:48:41,063
No. I can't!

1866
01:48:41,131 --> 01:48:44,123
Neither can you
or anybody else!

1867
01:48:44,201 --> 01:48:45,634
I'm just honest.

1868
01:48:45,702 --> 01:48:47,169
Stop being honest...

1869
01:48:47,237 --> 01:48:49,205
and start being generous!

1870
01:48:49,273 --> 01:48:50,740
Think about him!

1871
01:48:50,807 --> 01:48:53,776
What does he expect from me?

1872
01:48:53,844 --> 01:48:57,837
He wants a hug
when he passes exams?

1873
01:48:57,914 --> 01:49:00,906
I can't respond
when someone says...

1874
01:49:00,984 --> 01:49:03,953
"I did something
great. Love me."

1875
01:49:04,021 --> 01:49:08,014
He wants to know
you don't hate him.

1876
01:49:08,091 --> 01:49:10,582
Mothers don't hate their sons.

1877
01:49:10,661 --> 01:49:13,630
Is that what he told you?

1878
01:49:13,697 --> 01:49:17,690
You accept what he says
with no questions.

1879
01:49:17,768 --> 01:49:20,760
I'm trying to
keep this family...

1880
01:49:20,837 --> 01:49:23,806
What does everyone
want from me?

1881
01:49:23,874 --> 01:49:28,311
Listen. We all just
want you to be happy.

1882
01:49:28,378 --> 01:49:29,845
Happy?

1883
01:49:29,913 --> 01:49:30,880
Yes.

1884
01:49:30,947 --> 01:49:34,644
You tell me
the definition of happy.

1885
01:49:34,718 --> 01:49:37,983
First. Be sure your kids are safe...

1886
01:49:38,055 --> 01:49:41,547
that nobody's been hit by a car...

1887
01:49:41,625 --> 01:49:44,617
or drowned in your swimming pool!

1888
01:49:44,695 --> 01:49:48,187
Then tell me how to be happy!

1889
01:50:41,718 --> 01:50:44,186
I'm turning in.

1890
01:50:44,254 --> 01:50:45,721
Dinner was good.

1891
01:50:45,789 --> 01:50:47,256
Really good.

1892
01:50:47,324 --> 01:50:49,758
It's early. You tired?

1893
01:50:49,826 --> 01:50:52,090
It was a rough week.

1894
01:50:52,162 --> 01:50:55,893
Your grandmother
wasn't too tough on you?

1895
01:50:55,966 --> 01:50:57,934
No. She was fine.

1896
01:51:00,504 --> 01:51:03,029
I'm glad you're back.

1897
01:51:17,387 --> 01:51:18,854
Good night.

1898
01:52:37,634 --> 01:52:42,037
[Sobbing]

1899
01:52:48,779 --> 01:52:50,212
Calvin?

1900
01:53:02,159 --> 01:53:04,059
Why are you crying?

1901
01:53:10,901 --> 01:53:12,368
Can I. Uh...

1902
01:53:12,436 --> 01:53:14,904
Can I get you something?

1903
01:53:17,007 --> 01:53:18,474
I don't...

1904
01:53:18,542 --> 01:53:20,510
What did you say?

1905
01:53:24,681 --> 01:53:26,979
Calvin. What did you say?

1906
01:53:27,050 --> 01:53:28,574
[Sighing]

1907
01:53:31,521 --> 01:53:33,716
Tell me.

1908
01:53:40,364 --> 01:53:41,831
You are beautiful.

1909
01:53:45,435 --> 01:53:47,926
And you are unpredictable.

1910
01:53:50,040 --> 01:53:52,008
But you're so cautious.

1911
01:53:54,611 --> 01:53:56,044
You're determined. Beth...

1912
01:53:56,113 --> 01:53:58,240
but you know something?

1913
01:54:00,550 --> 01:54:02,142
You're not strong.

1914
01:54:04,254 --> 01:54:07,519
I don't know
if you're really giving.

1915
01:54:10,694 --> 01:54:12,184
Tell me something.

1916
01:54:12,262 --> 01:54:14,355
Do you love me?

1917
01:54:16,466 --> 01:54:18,934
Do you really love me?

1918
01:54:21,305 --> 01:54:25,139
I feel the way I've always
felt about you.

1919
01:54:37,754 --> 01:54:40,222
We would've been all right...

1920
01:54:40,290 --> 01:54:43,782
if there hadn't been any mess.

1921
01:54:45,395 --> 01:54:47,863
But you can't handle mess.

1922
01:54:49,466 --> 01:54:52,924
You need everything neat and easy.

1923
01:54:54,037 --> 01:54:55,504
I don't know.

1924
01:54:55,572 --> 01:54:58,040
Maybe you can't love anybody.

1925
01:54:58,108 --> 01:55:00,576
It was so much Buck.

1926
01:55:00,644 --> 01:55:05,638
It's as if you buried
all your love with him.

1927
01:55:05,716 --> 01:55:07,684
I don't understand that.

1928
01:55:09,286 --> 01:55:12,778
Maybe it wasn't even Buck.

1929
01:55:12,856 --> 01:55:15,256
Maybe it was just you.

1930
01:55:15,325 --> 01:55:20,957
Maybe, finally, it was
the best of you that you buried.

1931
01:55:23,533 --> 01:55:25,501
But whatever it was...

1932
01:55:29,139 --> 01:55:32,108
I don't know who you are.

1933
01:55:32,175 --> 01:55:36,669
I don't know what
we've been playing at.

1934
01:55:39,282 --> 01:55:41,409
So I was crying.

1935
01:55:45,922 --> 01:55:49,983
Because I don't know
if I love you anymore.

1936
01:55:53,030 --> 01:55:57,524
And I don't know
what I'll do without that.

1937
01:57:27,290 --> 01:57:28,222
[Door Slams]

1938
01:58:28,785 --> 01:58:29,877
Dad?

1939
01:58:33,123 --> 01:58:36,115
The yard looks smaller
without leaves.

1940
01:58:37,694 --> 01:58:39,161
Dad. What happened?

1941
01:58:41,264 --> 01:58:44,756
Your mother's
going away for a while.

1942
01:58:44,834 --> 01:58:45,994
Where?

1943
01:58:46,069 --> 01:58:47,297
Why?

1944
01:58:47,370 --> 01:58:48,837
Back to Houston.

1945
01:58:49,906 --> 01:58:51,373
I don't know.

1946
01:58:52,475 --> 01:58:53,908
Why? What...

1947
01:58:56,012 --> 01:58:57,479
I know why.

1948
01:58:57,547 --> 01:58:59,515
It's me. Isn't it?

1949
01:58:59,583 --> 01:59:00,550
No.

1950
01:59:00,617 --> 01:59:02,050
It's my fault.

1951
01:59:02,118 --> 01:59:04,382
Don't do that to yourself!

1952
01:59:04,454 --> 01:59:05,887
It's nobody's fault!

1953
01:59:05,956 --> 01:59:09,357
Things happen.
People don't always have answers.

1954
01:59:13,163 --> 01:59:16,963
I don't know why
I'm yelling at you.

1955
01:59:17,033 --> 01:59:20,127
You should do
that more often.

1956
01:59:20,203 --> 01:59:21,932
Haul my ass a little.

1957
01:59:22,005 --> 01:59:23,438
Get after me.

1958
01:59:25,775 --> 01:59:27,611
Like you did for him.

1959
01:59:27,744 --> 01:59:29,211
He needed it.

1960
01:59:29,279 --> 01:59:30,211
You didn't.

1961
01:59:30,280 --> 01:59:33,215
You were always
so hard on yourself.

1962
01:59:33,283 --> 01:59:35,615
I never had the heart.

1963
01:59:35,685 --> 01:59:38,210
Oh. Dad. Don't.

1964
01:59:38,288 --> 01:59:40,518
Well. It's the truth.

1965
01:59:42,292 --> 01:59:44,726
I never worried about you.

1966
01:59:44,794 --> 01:59:47,729
I just wasn't listening.

1967
01:59:48,865 --> 01:59:51,095
I wasn't sending
many signals then.

1968
01:59:51,167 --> 01:59:53,067
You couldn't do anything.

1969
01:59:53,136 --> 01:59:56,697
I should've got
a handle on it somehow.

1970
02:00:01,811 --> 02:00:05,747
I used to figure you had
a handle for everything.

1971
02:00:05,815 --> 02:00:08,045
You knew it all.

1972
02:00:08,118 --> 02:00:12,111
You always made us feel
everything would be all right.

1973
02:00:13,189 --> 02:00:16,158
I've thought about that
a lot lately.

1974
02:00:16,226 --> 02:00:18,694
I really admire you for it.

1975
02:00:18,762 --> 02:00:20,753
Don't admire people too much.

1976
02:00:20,830 --> 02:00:23,924
They'll disappoint you sometimes.

1977
02:00:25,068 --> 02:00:26,933
I'm not disappointed.

1978
02:00:30,106 --> 02:00:32,676
I love you.

1979
02:00:38,281 --> 02:00:39,714
I love you. Too.

